生態模型導論                            


  	Ecological research is based mainly upon three approaches; field observation, laboratory experiment, and theoretical prediction.  In this course, students can acquire basic knowledge and applied skills of theoretical approaches in ecological research.  Particular focus will be placed on long-term population dynamics and broad-scale spatial distribution of species and community, which are generally difficult to study in empirical approaches.  The course is mainly for undergraduates who are interested in ecology, though other fields of students can also be accepted.  High skills of computer programming and mathematics are not required to attend this course.

課程教育目標 

A. 培養具備整體（holistic）生命科學知能 
