基本素養 Basic Literacy
■ 生命科學基本認知
 Basic knowledges of life sciences
■ 實驗科學的態度
 Attitude for experimental science
■ 培養同理心、尊重包容的公民素養
 Develop the civic literacy of empathy, respect and inclusion
□ 對生命的社會關懷
 The social care of lives
□ 生態保育的哲學觀與正義思維
 The philosophy and justice thinking of ecological conservation
■ 跨領域學習與國際視野
 Interdisciplinary learning and global vision.
 

核心能力 Competence
■ 生命科學實驗操作及使用相關儀器的能力
 The experimental operation and the use of the insturments of life sciences
□ 具備獨立思考與判斷的能力
 Capable of thinking and judging independently
□ 具備有效溝通與解決問題的能力
 Capable of communicating effectively and solving the problem
■ 跨領域知識整合與創新能力
 Integration of interdisciplinary knowledges and ability to innovate
□ 展現團隊合作能力
 Capacity to show teamwork
 

課程概述 Course Description
       Ecological research is based mainly upon three approaches; field observation, laboratory experiment, and theoretical prediction.  In this course, students can acquire basic knowledge and applied skills of theoretical approaches in ecological research.  Particular focus will be placed on long-term population dynamics and broad-scale spatial distribution of species and community, which are generally difficult to study in empirical approaches.  The course is mainly for undergraduates who are interested in ecology, though other fields of students can also be accepted.  High skills of computer programming and mathematics are not required to attend this course.Ecological research is based mainly upon three approaches; field observation, laboratory experiment, and theoretical prediction.  In this course, students can acquire basic knowledge and applied skills of theoretical approaches in ecological research.  Particular focus will be placed on long-term population dynamics and broad-scale spatial distribution of species and community, which are generally difficult to study in empirical approaches.  The course is mainly for undergraduates who are interested in ecology, though other fields of students can also be accepted.  High skills of computer programming and mathematics are not required to attend this course.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    To learn basic knowledge and applied skills of theoretical approach in ecology
     

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1General introduction2Getting started with programming3Population growth I4Population growth II5Community I6Community II7Spatial structure8Age and stage structure9Disease and mutualism10Dynamics and stability I11Dynamics and stability II12Species richness estimate13Species Area relationship14Species distribution model I15Species distribution model II16Conservation applications I17Conservation applications II18Final integration 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


